HEADWORD: Tintinnabulum
<hw>Tin`tin*nab"u*lum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu>pl.
<plw>Tintinnabula</plw> <pr>(#)</pr></plu>. <ety>[L., a bell. See
<er>Tintinnabular</er>.]</ety> <def>A bell; also, a set or combination
of bells or metal plates used as a musical instrument or as a
toy.</def>⟦br⟧
